Line 311: if (!elementIsLate) { ... }                       // Merging windows guard
Line 415: if (!elementIsLate) { ... }                       // Non-merging windows guard
Line 452: if (isSkippedElement && isElementLate(element))   // Side output check (DIRECT CALL)
```

**Issue**: The variable is assigned but NOT reused at line 452 - the code calls `isElementLate(element)` again instead of reusing the cached boolean. This is a minor inefficiency.

**Recommendation**: Change line 452 from:
```java
